          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1630422060585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and most of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) to the pan then cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and cook for a further 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1630422064667-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1630422064667-x400.jpg",
